Transocean Appoints Shaw as Chief Controller, Accounting Officer

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-08-04T19:36:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/transocean-appoints-shaw-as-chief-controller-accounting-officer.html
Transocean Ltd. (RIG) , the world’s largest
offshore driller,  said  Rob Shaw has been appointed vice
president, controller and principal accounting officer effective
Dec. 1. He has been vice president and treasurer since July
2010.  Robert Herrin Jr. will be interim vice president and
controller, and Ricardo Rosa, the company’s senior vice
president and chief financial officer, will be interim principal
accounting officer, Transocean said in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Berlin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  